title: For Sale:  Hi Standard G380 (Rare)
postcontent: For sale in great condition! The G .380 began production in late in 1947, with serial numbers beginning at 100 and running up to 7551. A nice example of a hard to find well made .380 caliber pistol. The well known Hi Standard company only made about 7400 of these between 1947 and 1950. It was the only centerfire pistol that the company  made in house. There is a lever take down system, an exposed hammer, and handsome black checkered plastic grips. The overall condition rates 90-95%. The metal has a dark blue finish except for the top of the slide and barrel which have a dull blue finish to reduce glare on the sight line. There are some minor marks on to left side of the slide.
